            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Auxiliary Verbs: 'haben' and 'sein'"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The auxiliary verbs used on the <i>Perfekt</i> tense are <b>haben</b> and <b>sein</b>:"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Haben:</b> Used with most verbs:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich habe Gemüse gegessen.",
                            "text": "Ich <b>habe</b> Gemüse $__gegessen-essen[verb-link-hover]__$ ",
                            "translation": "(I have eaten vegetables)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Sein:</b> Used with verbs that indicate a change of state or movement (e.g., 'gehen' - to go, 'kommen' - to come):",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Er ist nach Berlin gefahren.",
                            "text": "Er <b>ist</b> nach Berlin $__gefahren-fahren[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(He went to Berlin)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "content": "It is very important to master the conjugations of <b>haben</b> and <b>sein</b> to learn the <i>Perfekt</i> tense:"
        },
